<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>So is a bow superior to a hand held melee weapon?</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?TheBlack">TheBlack</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 7:21 p.m. 17/5/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> So is a bow superior to a hand held melee weapon?<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=2059" TARGET=_self>Do you read any of the posts?</A> (Gray Rage (DB))
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>

<BR>I dueled fighters with my Shaman at low levels 8-13 and I beat them consistently. By buffing up ahead of time then being able to heal during the battle the warriors were unable to match me. Would a bow have evened the playing field for a warrior, or is that only of use vs running spellcasters?
<P>I also think fighters have their place in team melee situations. Having a damage absorbing tank that can lay into the enemy is definitely a plus.
<P>&gt; If you look down the board you will see posts regarding ways for
<BR>&gt; warriors to win PvP combat. Our Ladder even has a Warrior ON
<BR>&gt; TOP!
<P>&gt; The only reason you cannot beat a spell caster is probably the
<BR>&gt; same reason you picked warrior as your class in the first
<BR>&gt; place....you are not bright enough to play a spell caster (no
<BR>&gt; offense to warriros out there).
<P>&gt; Dude...a warrior can KICK a spell caster's ASS, if he just uses
<BR>&gt; his BRAIN. I really should not even respond to this as just a
<BR>&gt; couple of posts down give warriors GOOD info on HOW to defeat
<BR>&gt; any spell caster in combat. Do you even have a bow? There are
<BR>&gt; bows with 40 Delay 20+ Dam meaning 80+ dam. Your dual weild
<BR>&gt; double attack will WRECK a spell caster....heck most spell
<BR>&gt; casters will have to med in a battle with an EQUAL warrior type
<BR>&gt; just to have enough mana to KILL HIM!
<P>&gt; The only thing verant might change is a TRUE autoattack feature
<BR>&gt; which will have your character autofind and follow it's target
<BR>&gt; (just like the NPC's do). This will take away the packet loss or
<BR>&gt; lag problem with chasing a fleeing foe or finding a
<BR>&gt; shadowstepping one.
<P>&gt; Dude, instead of complaining....figure out how to win.
<P>&gt; -Gray
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
